AGI - "Meeting with the Vatican Secretary of State, Cardinal Pietro Parolin. During our conversation, special attention was paid to the path towards a just and lasting peace and to the efforts of Ukraine, the United States and Europe to establish a complete and unconditional ceasefire." He writes Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelensky on Telegram.
&nbsp;
"Thank you for supporting Ukraine's right to self-defense and the principle that there is no need to impose peace conditions on a victim country. We expect the Holy See to continue to contribute to the unification of international efforts to reach peace, the return of Ukrainian children deported from Russia and the liberation of prisoners." &nbsp;
<h2>Zelensky sees Zuppi, Vatican helps us for children
"To us today it is very important to be in Italy and join the whole world. We are grateful for the assistance that the Vatican provides to Ukraine in the return of Ukrainian children > illegally deported and displaced from Russia and in the release of prisoners", writes on Telegram the president of Ukraine Volodymyr Zelensky.
&nbsp;
"This theme was one of the most important of our meeting with Cardinal Matteo Zuppi. The most important thing for our state is to bring all our citizens home, from their loved ones, from their families. In Russia there are many children held against their will. We want to bring them home and that's why we turn to the Vatican again for this kind of help."

