&nbsp;
&nbsp;Meloni chose a single non-informal meeting, just with Ukrainian president in Chigi Palace, lasted about an hour. At the end of which the prime minister reiterated his support for Trump's efforts to achieve a just and lasting peace, "capable of guaranteeing a future of security, sovereignty and freedom to Ukraine" and expressed in Kiev its condolences for the victims of recent Russian attacks, renewing the firm condemnation of such acts.
Black Tailleur and dark glasses, the premier had made known, on the eve of the funerals of Pope Francis, that he did not want to organize official meetings. While the American president arrived in Rome with the intention to dictate the line to reach an understanding. >
He planned to see both the Ukrainian president and Macron and Starmer, but the talks did not take place at Villa Taverna, as at first it had been hypothesized, but just inside the church. With Zelensky (arrived in Rome in shirt and jacket, in dark dresses instead of the usual green mimetic) the meeting - lasted 15 minutes> - "was very productive", is leaked from the White House; "a very symbolic meeting that has the potential to become historic, if we reach joint results", wrote the Ukrainian president who presented a counterproposal to the American document.
In short, in the "name of Francis" > the 'negotiations of Rome' &nbsp; could represent an important junction on the path of peace, also thanks to the 'disgelo' signed between Zelensky and Trump. Meloni, in addition to this face-to-face face between the two leaders, then wanted to emphasize the efficiency of the <a href="https://www.agi.it/cronaca/news/20 A thanks - it has written in a note - to all the administrations involved and to the women and men of volunteering, "to all goes the thanks of the government and my staff for having guaranteed with professionalism, dedication and spirit of service the serene conduct of a historical day for Italy and for the world">. In 400 thousand (250 thousand at the funeral and 150 thousand on the way of the feretro between Saint Peter and Saint Mary Major) they wanted to greet the Holy Father.
<h2> An extraordinary day
"It was an extraordinary day that saw a great participation by both Roman citizens and faithful from all over the world," said the head of the Civil Protection department who, speaking with Agi, > remarked "the great result of the whole system" and especially "the excellent synergy" with the Prefecture. It is "a historical page for security", also seen "the greatness of the event", commented Interior Minister Matteo Piantedosi.
"It all went very well," Roberto Massucci claimed. Many heads of state and government will return to the first Mass that will be celebrated by the new Pope (presumably on May 25) but in the meantime the powerful of the world wanted to honor the deceased Holy Father, also trying to lay the foundations for the end of the war.&nbsp;
